senses.sense_text:
A man from the tribe of Judah living at the time of the New Testament, first mentioned at Mat.1.1; 
referred to as Jesus or "he" or Lord or Christ or [ ] (Ἰησοῦς), or Christ or [ ] (Χριστός), or Christian (Χριστιανός), or Immanuel (KJV= Emmanuel) (עִמָּנוּאֵל), or Immanuel (Ἐμμανουήλ); 
son of Joseph and Mary; 
a brother of James, Joses, Simon and Jude.
